data.text:
AWARDS

MAAC ALL- ACADEMIC TEAM (2021, 2022)

CAREER HIGHS

Goals: NA

Assists: 1, 3x, last vs. Iona (10/12/22)

Points: 1, 3x, last vs. Iona (10/12/22)

FALL 2022 • SENIOR SEASON

• Appeared in all 17 matches, making 14 starts; one of six players to appear in every game

• Played the full time in eight contests

• Appeared in over 1,000 minutes for the second-straight season

• Recorded two assists during the season - one vs. St. Bonaventure (Sept. 9) and vs. Iona (Oct. 12)

• Named to the MAAC All-Academic Team

FALL 2021 • JUNIOR SEASON

• Appeared in all 17 games

• Member of starting lineup for 16 games

• Played the full match 10 times

• Credited for four shots on goal

SPRING 2021 • SOPHOMORE SEASON

• Started all six games

• Played entirety of season finale versus Saint Peter's (April 5), earning first collegiate point with an assist

• Recorded shot attempts in last three games, including three in back-to-back games at Niagara (March 28) and at Manhattan (April 3)

BEFORE CANISIUS

• Attended UT Rio Grande Valley for one year, making Dean’s List in both semesters

• Played six seasons with Aurora FC under Don Ferguson, scoring 31 points over 22 games in last two seasons

• Was team captain on Aurora’s Under-21 team in 2018

• Earned four varsity letters at Cardinal Ambrozic Catholic Secondary, starting every game during senior year
